{"title":"What I’ve been reading","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/874458107/0/marginalrevolution~What-Ive-been-reading.html","date":1711434291000,"content":"<p>Christopher Phillips, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Battleground-Conflicts-that-Explain-Middle/dp/0300263422/ref=sr_1_1?crid=3CETDDJFR8Z12&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.suGiTm64njwZj2vXNjEpdTuOtQRc3h8MhK5EgaHF7cGmrad8WFevoeBvBoVpOsre9ucba8rQJsou6M0U2eN7HsoKEil8UCX9LF_zcy91oPMh9e2qjVB2il1usD7cH772ezcb4G5QsW3I_tR0b7iFLfVFhE9W5XZEQMWrALaoTwcd0y10G2Rnli7R9pTbJmiR.xeVctrp0XVw5JHrV9YqgCV8mPVWNcwnehWsRPOVF9Yk&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=christopher+phillips+battleground&amp;qid=1711409104&amp;sprefix=christopher+phillips%2Caps%2C76&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">Battle Ground: Ten Conflicts that Explain the New Middle East</a>.  A good, “simple enough” introduction to the wars going on in Syria, Yemen, and other parts of the Middle East.  If you are worried you will hate, you can just skip the Palestine chapter.</p>\r\n<p>Catherine Pakaluk, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Hannahs-Children-Quietly-Defying-Dearth/dp/1684514576/ref=sr_1_1?crid=Q14ZG06670OX&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.ItLeIqUJ-0TN2elOiYvA8_a_uF-JTrH2WKK86SNfw6q0i97lmmYwDBJ0HVFYdA1MDTJ1JkIzkyWdpUw1DqqPP_qW_nJ3SG99vgYueNEUz1I.2jvD8-WA3lb7K_IUDEMEQN1N-ngWZhFvGVBSRZksXIk&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Catherine+Pakaluk&amp;qid=1711409159&amp;sprefix=catherine+pakaluk%2Caps%2C75&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">Hannah’s Children: The Women Quietly Defying the Birth Dearth</a>.  About five percent of American women end up having five children or more — what do you learn by talking to them?  (“Which one should I give back?”)  The author herself has eight children.</p>\r\n<p>Beth Linker,<a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Slouch-Posture-Panic-Modern-America/dp/069123549X/ref=sr_1_1?crid=APH8NSXAT198&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.y_8lj9TxJLcmUt5nQezQlQ.TE0DEqOXp9iWC4TfrQYTqfwGlhR01ZajaInnIRv7oIc&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Slouch%3A+Posture+Panic+in+Modern+America&amp;qid=1711409191&amp;sprefix=slouch+posture+panic+in+modern+america%2Caps%2C81&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\"> Slouch: Posture Panic in Modern America</a>.  For a long time I’ve been thinking there should be a good book on this topic, and now there is one.  Both fun and interesting.</p>\r\n<p>Maxwell Stearns, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Parliamentary-America-Radically-Repairing-Democracy/dp/1421448335/ref=sr_1_1?crid=29AL6V1GKM7QX&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.qwNJ_9jfNvU1wanWcdruz9VbVGaIzgt5zfrOtpBevzLGjHj071QN20LucGBJIEps.rkb2NfNln2f5gU9yVLrdBjPNrFNa2-8jaX4u8_O2ucU&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Parliamentary+America%3A+The+Least+Radical+Means+of+Radically+Repairing+our+Broken+Democracy&amp;qid=1711409225&amp;sprefix=parliamentary+america+the+least+radical+means+of+radically+repairing+our+broken+democracy%2Caps%2C81&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">Parliamentary America: The Least Radical Means of Radically Repairing our Broken Democracy</a> argues for proportional representation and accompanying reforms.  Putting aside whether this ever can happen, I am never quite sure how this is supposed to work when nuclear weapons use is such a live issue.</p>\r\n<p>Ethan Mollick is the best and most thorough Twitter commentator on LLMs, he now has a forthcoming book <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Co-Intelligence-Living-Working-Ethan-Mollick/dp/059371671X/ref=sr_1_1?crid=2GUSEWJSSSRPO&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.WKSFtpG0prEg-rqFzXHbpqIwb875sOJAbO4IFbzf_GwK9NPCwsmy6U6E0CwyB4K32IMwpaQcyE5a8wAvrREppJYA69UWrBIMX9N9TEpESIk.SBO4A46GV6XXV7A5pU3as6dYGI8FLNy7R641HpaW4TI&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=ethan+mollick+co-intelligence&amp;qid=1710381504&amp;sprefix=ethan+mollick%2Caps%2C73&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">Co-Intelligence</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Andrew Leigh, an Australian MP and also economist, has published <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.google.com/search?q=andrew+leigh+The+Shortest+History+of+Economics&amp;sca_esv=2cdbf9d7674441ef&amp;source=hp&amp;ei=gQgCZpykMIvt5NoPtYmvoA4&amp;iflsig=ANes7DEAAAAAZgIWkVpCO_TVlEkrV2-rqDo77_snzs-I&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjc6LmyyJCFAxWLNlkFHbXEC-QQ4dUDCBc&amp;uact=5&amp;oq=andrew+leigh+The+Shortest+History+of+Economics&amp;gs_-UB&amp;sclient=gws-wiz\" target=\"_blank\">The Shortest History of Economics</a>, recommended by Claudia Goldin.</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/03/what-ive-been-reading-250.html\">What I’ve been reading</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" src=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/i/874458107/0/marginalrevolution\" />\r\n<div><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/28/874458107/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/fblike20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/29/874458107/marginalrevolution,\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/pinterest20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/24/874458107/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/x.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/19/874458107/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/email20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/20/874458107/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/rss20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/03/what-ive-been-reading-250.html#comments\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/comments20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https